Unlink and Symlink linux bash (downgrade python 2.7 to python 2.6)
Python environment in linuxmint 11 (on april 2012) is using python 2.7, but some package is not works in there. So we want to downgrade it to python 2.6

first, install python2.6 :
sudo apt-get install python2.6

unlink python envi :
sudo unlink /usr/bin/python

link it to python2.6 :
sudo ln -s /usr/bin/python2.6 /usr/bin/python
